Vietnamese species. Eight species has been recognized by us from Vietnam: 
canina
(Brown & Boisvert) [= sp. eg-2] (Tay Yen Tu); 
dohertyi
(Emery) [= sp. eg-1] (Ba Vi, Sa Pa, Tay Yen Tu, Tam Dao, Van Ban); 
kichijo
(Terayama, Lin et Wu) [= sp. eg-5] (Cuc Phuong); 
japonica
(Ito) [= sp. eg-6] (Sa Pa); mitis Brown [= sp. eg-3] (Ba Vi, Cuc Phuong, Nam Cat Tien); 
nepalensis
(De Andrade) [= sp. eg-4] (Ba Be); sp. eg-7 (My Yen, Van Ban); sp. eg-8 (Nam Cat Tien).
